There's a common pattern I do a lot in my code:

`
export const Classes = [];

class BaseClass {
  static register(childClass) {
    Classes.push(childClass);
  }
}

class Child extends BaseClass {
}
BaseClass.register(Child);
`

Angular's webpack setup (at least Angular 10) prunes child classes that use this pattern.
I don't understand why; shouldn't `BaseClass.register(Child)` be enough to keep them around?

